fields.name: CH24 Y-CHAIR
fields.description: The CH 24 Y chair was designed by Hans J. Wegner in 1949 and has been manufactured without interruption since 1950. Also called the Wishbone chair, it is a true icon among chairs and hotly sought after by collectors around the world. The comfortable shape provides a high level of comfort and good mobility.

fields.name: LAMINO ARMCHAIR
fields.description: This Lamino is a beautiful, comfortable armchair with light, Scandinavian shapes. It was named Swedish furniture of the century in 1999 and is Nordic Ecolabelled. The armchair is made of layer-glued and molded veneer in various wooden alternatives with sheepskin, leather or fabric upholstery. Eco-labeled with the Swan.

fields.name: CH327
fields.description: Dining table CH327 was designed for Carl Hansen & Son by Hans J. Wegner in 1962. CH327 is the ultimate dining table in solid wood, but also works well as a desk or conference table.

fields.name: PK61
fields.description: In 1956, the PK61 coffee table was designed, with which Poul Kjærholm shows a clear development from industrial designer to furniture architect. The four parts of the base are assembled by machine screws and give the coffee table an industrial and sophisticated appearance. The removable table top is held in place with the help of gravity - a style feature that is significant to Kjærholm.

fields.name: Nati tati
fields.description: The bedside table Nati Tati, designed by Mats Broberg and Johan Ridderstråle for Asplund, fits most bed styles. The design language in the series combines soft and strict shapes with unexpected materials and colors.

fields.name: COLLECT 2013 CABINET
fields.description: Here we present Collect 2013, a nice cabinet with doors made of round rods in two versions, one colorful and one white.

fields.name: LEVIER UNIT 2/5 SHELF WALL
fields.description: Levier wall shelf is designed by Cate & Nelson for Voice. The elegant and simple design makes it fit in most rooms. Levier wall shelf is made of ash with shelves of ash veneer in two colors, natural lacquer and black-blue lacquer.

fields.name: TREE COAT RACK WALL HIGH
fields.description: Tree is a nice and practical coat hanger that fits in most rooms.

fields.name: Snowball pendant
fields.description: PH Snowball by Poul Henningsen provides a soft and pleasant light. PH Snowball is an excellent example of what Louis Poulsen strives for: to create lamps that the eye never tires of looking at.

fields.name: Snoopy
fields.description: Snoopy table lamp from Flos, designed by Achille Castiglioni and Pier Giacomo Castiglioni in 1967. Snoopy has a white marble lamp base and a screen in lacquered black metal.

fields.name: Panthella Floor lamp
fields.description: Verner Panton's floor lamp Panthella has achieved almost cult-like status. The organic and well-balanced shape makes the lamp a sculpture in itself.

fields.name: TARAXACUM 88 C/W
fields.description: Taraxacum 88 C / W is a wall lamp designed in 1988 by Achille Castiglioni for Flos. With 15 light bulbs attached to a frame of equilateral triangles, Taraxacum 88 C / W is an awesome wall lamp and a work of art in itself.

fields.name: Elk lamp
fields.description: Really worn and old wall light.

fields.name: Sebastian Tirsén
fields.description: Jag är superimponerad! Vilket geni har byggt denna fantastiska ratingfunktion?
